5:
All right, that takes care of the
shopping! Thanks for tagging along,
Reylas.
8:
Consider it thanks for all your
assistance. I eagerly await your next
culinary concoction.
21:
I just remembered an errand I must
run. Head back without me.
27: Huh? Wait, where are you going?!
33:
Surely there are faster ways to
contact me than bribing a glorified
carrier pigeon.
36:
Well? I'm here, just like you wanted.
Show yourself, Altair!
41:
Well, look who it is... My dear big
brother! Sorry about giving you the
slip for so long!
42:
You see, I had to work on controlling
this new eye of mine. It certainly is
an unruly beast.
43:
I always knew you were amazing,
but I can't believe you've been able
to control this since birth.
45: Enough talk. Why are you here now?
48:
Well, aren't you impressed? Now I'm
just as amazing as you.
49:
It took hard work, you know. I had to
do lots and LOTS of practice, but
look at how far my magic has come!
52:
Don't tell me... all those victims were
just practice?
55:
Our family, our people! Was
everyone just a part of your little
game?
61:
These powers have been my burden
to bear since birth. They are my
responsibility.
64:
You have used them to commit
terrible transgressions. I cannot turn
a blind eye to this, Altair. Prepare
yourself!
67:
As cool as ever. You never fail to
impress. So you wanna play? Fine by
me... It'll be just like old times!
69:
Are you holding back? Or is this all
you've got?
72:
As much as I'm loath to admit it, this
is all I can muster...
74:
The brother you know is gone. He
died the moment you stole that eye.
However, I will not let that—
77: No... No, no, no, no, NO!
79:
My brother could NEVER be this
weak. NO ONE could surpass him.
ALL groveled at his feet. My brother
is the BEST OF THE BEST!
80:
My brother is not WEAK. I REFUSE to
believe that!
82:
So this is the extent of your ice
magic... We're done here.
92:
That's my brother for you. It's almost
infuriating.
94:
Next time, your right eye will be
mine. With that, I will become you,
and all of this will end.
104:
Of course. I never intended to hide it
anyway.
107:
That was Altair Oraclus. He is the
one responsible for the recent
attacks and the theft of my left eye...
He is also my little brother.
112:
I see... That explains why you're
always harping on about how this is
your responsibility.
116:
I wasn't able to save my brother,
and this is the price I must pay. It's
as simple as that, Champion.
123:
My clan have studied the Oculus for
generations. Sadly, that means they
value the strength of one's Oculus
above all else.
126:
Two brothers were born into this
clan. One possessed the strongest
Oculus ever seen, making him the
next head of the family. The other...
bore no Oculus at all.
130:
I saw the abuse of power and unjust
nature of the world... I told myself I
would fix it all for my brother, but...
133: Ha... Hahahaha! I did it! I finally did it!
134:
Now, I can be just like you, dear
brother!
141:
It seems all I did was make him
resent me even more.
146:
Deal with him yourself, right? Cause
everything's your fault? You've got it
all wrong, Mr. Head Honcho.
149:
I'm sick of hearing men drunk on
power babble on about atonement
and responsibility, like the world
revolves around them or something.
152: Are you implying that's what I am?
156:
Heh. It's even worse when they're
drunk on power they don't have
anymore.
161:
In any case, you should rest now. We
can come up with a strategy to deal
with your brother later.
165:
I can make something easy on the
stomach, but are you feeling up to
eating?
169:
Yes, I think so. I apologize for the
trouble.
173:
It seems you all intend to join my
cause.
176:
I trust that you will not run off on
your own.
180:
I assure you I have more sense than
that. I understand that my chances
of success are slim on my own.
183:
Drunk on power I no longer have...
Regardless of whether that's true or
not...
185: It is clear that I was arrogant.
188:
Then it may be best to ask the
others for assistance.
190:
You don't want to repeat my
mistakes, Reylas.
195: Altair... Everyone... I am so sorry...
